    "comment": "Rationale: Fig.1: \"Expression pattern of Kcnab2 transcripts encoding for the Kvβ2 protein in the developing CNS\"\n- \"On ultrastructural level Kvβ2 is located at postsynaptic sites in the PSD, visualized by pre-embedded immuno-electron microscopy (Fig. 1G). In subfractions of rat brain protein lysate Kvβ2 is present in all fractions except mitochondria and is enriched in the postsynaptic density. \"\n\nFig.2: \"ProSAP2/Shank3 interacts with Kvβ2 via its PDZ/PRR domain\"\n\nFig.3: \"Kvβ2 is interacting with the PDZ/PRR motifs of ProSAP2/Shank3 and is recruited into the clusters of ProSAP2/Shank3\"\n\n28/3/2018 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: - \"Cell culture experiments of rat hippocampal primary neurons...\"",
